OL,6,GBBC regional TV and local radio
OL,7,Gservices have been affected by strike
OL,8,Gaction by members of the National
OL,9,GUnion of Journalists.
OL,11,FThe NUJ said it expected 900 staff to
OL,12,Fjoin the 24-hour walkout, which began
OL,13,Fat 11am today.
OL,15,FThe union says the BBC's plans to
OL,16,Fmerge some local radio programmes
OL,17,Fwould "undermine already hollowed out
OL,18,Flocal radio content across England".
OL,20,FThe BBC said would try to minimise
OL,21,Fdisruption as much as possible.
OL,3,C24-hour NUJ strike affects BBC
OL,4,Cservices in England
