OL,6,FThe proposals for more local radio
OL,7,Fstations to share programming would
OL,8,F"see no overall reduction in staffing
OL,9,Flevels or local funding" and deliver
OL,10,F"even greater value to communities",
OL,11,Fa BBC spokesperson said.
OL,13,FOn TV, most English regions were
OL,14,Funable to broadcast regional news
OL,15,Fprogramming at 1.30pm, 6.30pm and
OL,16,F10.30pm. In these regions, an edition
OL,17,Fof Planet Earth was shown at 1.30pm.
OL,18,FGarden Rescue filled the 6.30pm slot
OL,19,Fand at 10.30pm a simulcast of the BBC
OL,20,FNews Channel was broadcast (a
OL,21,FSportsday bulletin).
OL,3,C24-hour NUJ strike affects BBC
OL,4,Cservices in England
